mass_flipper <- ggplot(data = penguins, 
                       aes(x = flipper_length_mm,
                           y = body_mass_g)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = species, 
                 shape = species),
             size = 3,
             alpha = 0.8) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("darkorange","purple","cyan4")) +
  labs(title = "Penguin size, Palmer Station LTER",
       subtitle = "Flipper length and body mass for Adelie, Chinstrap and Gentoo Penguins",
       x = "Flipper length (mm)",
       y = "Body mass (g)",
       color = "Penguin species",
       shape = "Penguin species") +
  theme(legend.position = c(0.2, 0.7),
        plot.title.position = "plot",
        plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 0, face= "italic"),
        plot.caption.position = "plot")

Proponer un modelo en el que el peso tiene una distribución normal con parámetros MU y SIGMA, donde MU se basa en el largo de las aletas.

PESO ~ NORMAL(MU, SIGMA) MU ~ largoAleta * alpha + beta alpha ~ normal(75,20) beta ~ normal(3000, 600) SIGMA ~ exponential(1/1000)

# modelo lineal - bayes
priors =  c( 
            prior(normal(75, 20), class = "b", coef ="flipper_length_mm"),
             prior(normal(0, 2000), class = "Intercept"),
            prior(exponential(0.001), class = "sigma")
             )

penguinFit <- brm(body_mass_g ~ flipper_length_mm, data =penguins,
                       family = gaussian,

                       prior = priors ,
                       chains = 4, iter = 5000*2, seed = 84735)

2 Proponer un modelo de regresión logística para clasificar a un pinguino como de la especie Gentoo usando como variable predictora al largo del pico (bill_length).

Probabilidad sea especie Gentoo = 1/(1+e^(alphabill_length + beta)) Logit(especieGentoo) ~ normal(alphabill_length + beta, sigma) alpha ~ normal(0, 5) beta ~ normal(0,100) sigma ~ exponential(1/1000)

newdata <- one_hot(as.data.table(penguins))
dfpen = newdata[,c("species_Gentoo","bill_length_mm")]
dfpen
logisticFitPenguin <- brm(formula = species_Gentoo ~ bill_length_mm,  
           data    = dfpen, 
           family  = bernoulli(link = "logit"),
           prior   = c(prior(normal(0, 100), class = "Intercept"),
                       prior(normal(0, 5), class = "b", coef = "bill_length_mm")),
           iter = 1000, warmup = 500, chains = 2,)
